SELECT sell_date, COUNT(DISTINCT product) AS num_sold, 
       GROUP_CONCAT(
                    DISTINCT product
                    ORDER BY product
                    SEPARATOR ","
                    ) AS products 
FROM Activities 
GROUP BY sell_date
ORDER BY sell_date;

Note:
The GROUP_CONCAT() function in Mysql is used to concatenate data from multiple rows into one field.
GROUP_CONCAT([DISTINCT] col_name1
             [ORDER BY clause]
		         [SEPARATOR str_val])
